      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PACKHAM PUNCH (5) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 8 lengths at this track in a handy 25.33. Has a tricky draw to overcome but has a good record over this journey. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. In sparkling form and looks the one to beat again. RITZA LAW (3) was an impressive winner last time in quickest of the meeting when scoring by 13 lengths (25.20) at this track. Has good speed and aided by a low draw. Looks a primary danger. AYRTON HERRERA (1) doesn't have the best strike-rate but recent form is sound. Has finished in the placings two on end now, the latest when second (25.89) at this track. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Leading chance. FIRE SONG (2) cannot be overlooked following a recent top-three finish.",
